The paper discusses a technique to protect chip design intellectual property from reverse engineering, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the implementation and evaluation of the proposed scheme, which involves low-cost and generic full-chip layout camouflaging, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), embedded systems (cs.ET), software engineering (cs.SE), and architecture (cs.AR).
